  "about": "Paris Sciences et Lettres (PSL) University is a public research university located in Paris, France. Formally created in 2019, with its project established in 2010 and its oldest constituent school dating back to 1530, PSL is a collegiate university comprising 11 schools. It offers interdisciplinary education across science, engineering, humanities, social sciences, fine art, and performing arts, awarding Bachelor's, Master's, and PhD degrees. PSL is renowned for its research excellence, boasting 28 Nobel laureates, 11 Fields Medalists, and numerous other distinguished alumni and staff.",
